Or reincarnation, 
so help me Ruben.

108
00:04:48,066 --> 00:04:49,733
- I'm not a bank machine.

109
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:50,833
- If you're worried about lunch,

110
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:51,866
stop it right now.

111
00:04:51,866 --> 00:04:53,933
Lunch is not a problem.

112
00:04:53,933 --> 00:04:55,533
Come on, we're late.

113
00:04:57,766 --> 00:04:59,066
This is what I'm talking about.

114
00:04:59,066 --> 00:05:01,066
Look at this.

115
00:05:01,066 --> 00:05:02,300
You wanna give me an investment?

116
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:04,333
Give me a public company 
that does scaffolding.

117
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:05,733
That's an investment.

118
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:08,000
Goddamn scaffolding's 
taking over the city.

119
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
- I don't think scaffolding's 
publicly traded.

120
00:05:12,266 --> 00:05:13,433
- You know something?

121
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:14,833
I'm serious about coffee.

122
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,366
Coffee, I'm better with it.

123
00:05:17,366 --> 00:05:19,433
Without coffee I've got 
nothing going for me.

124
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:21,133
- [Ruben] Yeah, but your heart.

125
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,466
- What about my heart?

126
00:05:23,466 --> 00:05:26,033
I've been asleep for six 
months with herbal tea.

127
00:05:26,033 --> 00:05:27,233
What's the point?

128
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:29,233
Coffee makes all the 
difference in the world.

129
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:32,066
Let me tell you something.

130
00:05:32,066 --> 00:05:33,200
Before I gave up coffee,

131
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,133
there was a lot.

132
00:05:34,133 --> 00:05:35,166
There was a lot.

133
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:36,466
Believe me.

134
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,700
There was a lot, believe me.

135
00:05:45,866 --> 00:05:47,266
Oh damn.

136
00:05:47,266 --> 00:05:48,200
Son of a bitch.

137
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,433
This is what I'm talking about.

138
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,200
What are you waiting for?

139
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,166
Don't you wanna meet her?

140
00:05:54,166 --> 00:05:55,466
Keep walking.

141
00:05:55,466 --> 00:05:56,433
- [Ruben] What do you 
mean keep walking?

142
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:57,766
- Keep walking, don't look.

143
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,633
I said don't look.

144
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:07,566
What is that?

145
00:06:07,566 --> 00:06:08,866
- You looked.

146
00:06:08,866 --> 00:06:09,866
- Yeah, I looked.

147
00:06:09,866 --> 00:06:11,400
I looked, but the both of us

148
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,500
standing there like 
a couple of idiots.

149
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,633
You ruined it.

150
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:15,866
- Did you see her?

151
00:06:15,866 --> 00:06:17,300
- [Lenny] No, I 
couldn't see anything.

152
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,300
Did you see her?

153
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,833
- How do I know if I saw her?

154
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:20,966
- Did you see the most 
beautiful creature

155
00:06:20,966 --> 00:06:22,266
on God's green earth?

156
00:06:22,266 --> 00:06:23,333
[Lenny] No.

157
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,366
- Then you didn't see her.

158
00:06:25,366 --> 00:06:26,866
- Now what?

159
00:06:26,866 --> 00:06:27,966
- Her appointment is at ten.

160
00:06:27,966 --> 00:06:29,300
It's 10:15, she's in there.

161
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,800
- [Ruben] 10:20.

162
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,533
- Your watch is fast.

163
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:34,800
- Yours is slow.

164
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,800
- You're always fast, 
and you always forget.

165
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,833
You're too young to forget.

166
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,233
Why don't you remember?

167
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,766
- Ten o'clock you say?

168
00:06:41,766 --> 00:06:43,266
- For three weeks 
since I spied her,

169
00:06:43,266 --> 00:06:45,033
she's been here at 
ten on Tuesday's,

170
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:47,066
and then she hops 
the bus to Sachs.

171
00:06:47,066 --> 00:06:48,766
- And meanwhile?

172
00:06:48,766 --> 00:06:50,400
- [Lenny] We wait.

173
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,233
- We're poking out 
like a sore thumb.

174
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:57,066
How about there?

175
00:06:57,066 --> 00:06:58,633
- I don't frequent those places.

176
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:00,200
- [Ruben] What places?

177
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,533
- There's no table service.

178
00:07:01,533 --> 00:07:03,533
- Table service, 
that's a good one.

179
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:04,700
He wants table service

180
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,500
to discuss his 
latest infatuation.

181
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:11,033
- Infatuation?

182
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:12,933
Infatuation sounds lascivious.

183
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:14,000
That's not me.

184
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,933
I'm respectful, I'm cordial.

185
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:17,900
Dignified.

186
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,633
Wouldn't you say?

187
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:22,966
Ruben?

188
00:07:22,966 --> 00:07:24,833
- I'd say terrifying.

189
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:26,133
- Not what I'm looking for.

190
00:07:27,766 --> 00:07:29,000
- Is that her?

191
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,133
- No.

192
00:07:30,133 --> 00:07:32,166
Her I would not be terrified.

193
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,733
Besides, she's not my type.

194
00:07:35,733 --> 00:07:38,900
This one, the one we're 
waiting for is special.

195
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,333
She reminds me of Ester.

196
00:07:42,233 --> 00:07:43,700
- [Ruben] Lenny.

197
00:07:44,966 --> 00:07:47,000
- What time is it?

198
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,433
- 11:15.

199
00:07:48,433 --> 00:07:51,033
11:10 according to your watch.

200
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:52,333
- It's 11:12.

201
00:07:53,933 --> 00:07:56,100
- [Waitress] There you go.

202
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,400
- You're not from here.

203
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,800
- No.

204
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,266
- Upstate then?

205
00:08:00,266 --> 00:08:02,233
Where you from?

206
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:04,033
- [Waitress] Washington state.

207
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:08,300
- That's, that's 
a beautiful place.

208
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:09,400
I've never been there.

209
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,166
- He never been anywhere.

210
00:08:11,166 --> 00:08:13,066
(laughing)

211
00:08:13,066 --> 00:08:15,900
- Italy, and Jersey, 
when I was ten,

212
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:17,600
but I remember everything.

213
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,900
That's a beautiful place.

214
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,666
- Well, this is a 
beautiful place too.

215
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,266
- You make it more beautiful.

216
00:08:22,266 --> 00:08:23,900
- Oh, thank you.

217
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,466
- And you say you can't 
talk to a pretty girl.

218
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:31,066
What do you call that?

219
00:08:31,066 --> 00:08:32,633
- That one, she's a kiss.

220
00:08:33,966 --> 00:08:35,333
I always liked the waitress.

221
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,000
That's why I like 
the table service.

222
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,133
No table service, no waitress.

223
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:40,400
That's what I'm talking about.

224
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:41,633
They approach you, they smile,

225
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:44,300
they talk to you, 
they bring you food.

226
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:48,033
I always like the waitress.

227
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:50,666
- Hey, my wife's 
getting a raise.

228
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:51,933
Big one.

229
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:54,100
Big position change 
for her over there.

230
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,166
- Good.

231
00:08:55,166 --> 00:08:56,033
Good for you.

232
00:08:56,033 --> 00:08:57,066
Good for your wife.

233
00:08:57,066 --> 00:08:58,000
Let me ask you something.

234
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,233
Why do you call her your wife?

235
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:01,666
Her name is Marcy.

236
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,233
The way you say, my wife,

237
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,066
it's as though you're 
discovering for 
the first time...

238
00:09:05,066 --> 00:09:06,300
- She is my wife.

239
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,733
- A man who has been 
married 25 years

240
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:09,066
talking to his lifelong friend

241
00:09:09,066 --> 00:09:11,233
shouldn't call 
his wife his wife.

242
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:12,400
He should call her 
by her first name,

243
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,433
which in this case is Marcy.

244
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:16,366
Now, if you were divorced,

245
00:09:16,366 --> 00:09:18,266
had a wife and an ex-wife,

246
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:19,666
then I could understand 
the differentiation

247
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:22,300
between the wife 
and the ex-wife,

248
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:23,800
but even then I think 
it would be more natural

249
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:26,000
for you to call them 
by their first names.

250
00:09:29,066 --> 00:09:31,000
What kind of money 
are we talking about?

251
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,666
- I don't know.

252
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:34,300
She thinks maybe 
close as twice as much

253
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:36,100
as what she's making now.

254
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:40,233
- Very interesting 
woman, your wife.

255
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:41,533
- Now what does that mean?

256
00:09:41,533 --> 00:09:43,966
- It means you should leave her.

257
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:46,833
- Is that her?

258
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:48,766
- Of course not.

259
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,833
- You got something 
on your face.

260
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:55,633
- What?

261
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:56,300
- I don't know what.

262
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,433
Here, let me.

263
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,200
- [Lenny] What is it?

264
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,500
- I don't know.

265
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,766
Cake?

266
00:10:03,766 --> 00:10:05,666
- I was not eating cake.

267
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,866
- It looks like cake.

268
00:10:07,866 --> 00:10:10,233
- My face is turning to cake.

269
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,333
I can't do this, my 
face is falling off.

270
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:16,400
- Oh, you look fine.

271
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,233
- Who do I think I am?

272
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:20,833
- You're Lenny, a fine 
looking gentleman.

273
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,400
